
This notebook covers the concept of **Hypothesis Testing** in statistics. It demonstrates how to test assumptions about data using statistical tests such as t-tests, chi-square tests, and ANOVA.

## 📂 Contents
- Formulating null and alternative hypotheses  
- Types of hypothesis tests  
- Performing statistical tests using `scipy`  
- Interpreting p-values and test results  

## 🛠️ Requirements
- Python 3.x
- Jupyter Notebook
- Libraries: `numpy`, `pandas`, `scipy`, `statsmodels`

You will gain hands-on experience in performing hypothesis testing and interpreting statistical test results for real-world problems.

